    "The score is then normalised to range between 0 and 1, where a perfect classifier receives a score of 1 for correctly predicting the true labels, and an inactive classifier gets a score of 0 for always predicting the normal class.",
    "The scoring metric fully acknowledges and rewards accurate diagnoses while granting partial credit to misdiagnoses with similar risks or outcomes as the true diagnosis.",
    "Figure 8 presents the most commonly used performance metrics in the selected studies.",
    "Among these metrics, sensitivity was the most frequently used, appearing in 139 papers.",
    "Accuracy and specificity followed, being utilised in 100 and 91 studies, respectively."
